	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It might also have something to do that SD Card Association hadn't published the <a href="http://www.sdcard.org/developers/tech/pls/" class="postlink">non-confidential simplified specs</a> to read SD cards when the PowerPak was first designed. Sure, it could have been designed with the FPGA doing most of the grunt work in collecting both nibbles or even clocking SPI eight times. But I guess at the time, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parallel_ATA" class="postlink">parallel ATA</a> was better documented, being a subset of ISA.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


