	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Just thought I'd weigh in here, since it's been a while. The first round of hardware will likely ship to its owners soon, after which I am happy to release instructions and code for building these. They are quite cheap parts-wise, and pretty simple to build. Given the cost (less than $30 in parts to build if you're thrifty, even less if you're building a bunch of them or already have parts) I think the capability is pretty good. MMC1 with CHR RAM and WRAM, and also two NROMs on the cart at the same time, and a simple USB interface.
<br />
<br />Release details and whatnot are coming. Thanks!
<br />
<br />EDIT: Oh, and one other thing, I do intend to offer pre-programmed Flash chips for people, as well as making completed cartridges. This stuff will be licensed under some kind of non-commercial license, but I won't really care if you have your buddy make you a chip and even pay him for it. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> Not like I can do anything, but it's nice to ask politely.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
